I’ve always wanted to make videos. I wanted to be the one to be able to inspire and to help push people to surpass limits and to continue admirably no matter the shit or obstacles one could face in their life. I was never one to do much talking, I just wanted the work to show. We are all students under the iron and with one common goal, to strengthen ourselves wether it be mental or physical, no matter the path, to hopefully unit us all, support each other through it, and reach new heights we never thought we could go. Here’s a little snippet of my very last powerlifting meet after taking a very long break, but my first to have my firstborn daughter there to see daddy do his thing. #discipline #motivated #isymfs #powerlifting #uspa #legendary #ironaddict #bodybuilding #dadbod #dadstrength

The stronger you get the more weight you have to throw up, I am only human and I get scared of the weight sometimes…. Allot of the times, I have to remind myself input my self through so much hard work when training I’m stronger than this. That’s what @jaysmyname taught me. Coach @ollaaay has me here 3x405x3 and as you can see the first two went up so well that the third should of went the same but I got in my head at the third and this is what happens, instead of just going for it right after the second. I know I am capable, I just have to tell myself that more. But I’m not worried it’s only the second week of prep 😎  #discipline #powerlifting #dadbod #dadswholift #bodybuilding #bench #legendary
